##I'm around Wuhan, trying my best to live a normal life

WECHAT betteryourlife2013

The feature introduces better your life, focusing on the better you and the better world that comes with it.

From the day of the "city closure" in Wuhan, our life began to "14 days" as a unit of calculation.

But Wuhan this city, also has been in the people line of Sight Focus most center.
New Year's Eve, the only stage on the Spring Festival has not rehearsed in the program, shouted out the first "Wuhan Refueling" ;
On the first day of the Lunar New Year, many medical teams from all over the country went to assist Wuhan
At 8 pm on the 27th, the citizens of Wuhan Spontaneously Sang "I and my motherland" at their windows
On the 28th, Academician Zhong Nanshan said in a tearful interview: "Wuhan is a city of heroes. "
â€¦â€¦
February 2, Vulcan Mountain official delivery, February 3 official admission of patients;
On February 5th, Mount Thor opened;
In the early hours of February 7, Dr Li Wenliang passed away at Wuhan Central Hospital.
Wuhan people in the attention and help, hobbled through the "first 14 days" , in Wuhan's 9 million people know, these 14 days, we walk not easy. On February 7, the "Four heavenly regiments" of the Chinese medical community met in Wuhan, and in the "second 14 days, " Wuhan is undoubtedly still the focus.
Data show that nearly half of the more than 5 million people who left Wuhan returned to the surrounding cities.

But at the same time, you may forget, these 14 days also go hard, there are more than 3 million left Wuhan, Wuhan back around the "New Wuhan People. ". At ordinary times, they are around us, working, studying, settling down, and building Wuhan with us.

Now, where are they? Have they had a good 14 days?

Lantern Festival, the second day of "the second 14 days" . Huang Xingyang learned from the gong-knocker in the village that a little girl in the bay next door was missing. She was in her twenties. On the same day, Huang Xingyang's father, finished the statistics of each household needs of materials, the village committee unified procurement.

On the day of the Lantern Festival, the village committee for the first time counted the materials needed by the villagers

Because parents year-round in the home, the family has food reserves, their own home also planted some vegetables, Huang Xingyang family by road closure impact is not big. "But some of them are from out of town and haven't bought much food at all. The vendors are almost out of business, and the passers-by don't let people out easily. I don't know how long those who don't have food can last, how poor they are. "

A small shop in the bay is still selling vegetables, although the vegetables have withered, or someone to buy. "I don't know how long it will be open. Fortunately, the village committee has started counting the material demand. "

Huang Xingyang family's material reserve is very sufficient

Wanzi, where Huang Xingyang lives, was closed until the third day of the Lunar New Year. The main road leading to the town was blocked, as was the road to the bay next door.

Boulders, hewn-down trees, mounds of earth... materials once used to pave the road have all been turned into blocking tools. In and out of the intersection of the bay, the person on duty guarding the road, Gong people shouted "do not go out, go out wearing a mask" , a bay of a bay shuttle, publicity.

There are "checkpoints" at the different exits of Wanzi

Close "blockade" measures, people every day to take body temperature... although Huang Xingyang in Wanzi, the first 14 days after the absence of confirmed and suspected cases, but everyone is very alert. "after all, people's lives are at stake. There are confirmed cases in the bay next door. Can we ignore them? "

Neighborhood neighbors no longer visit, the scene of large-scale poker in the past no, meet acquaintances at home activities, all maintain 8 meters away from the simple greetings, and then go home. A village without the flavor of the year, but now it is reassuring.

Because masks are limited, villagers who have been away for a short time are kept at a safe distance

The first 14 days are over, the year is over. Huang Xingyang will not be red-faced because his elders want to visit relatives, he is more worried about the situation in Wuhan, "the community is also closed that everyone how to purchase supplies? Can Not cross-district admission, can ensure that all patients can be admitted? "
Learning from his circle of friends that his friends and relatives are safe for the time being, Huang Xingyang can not see the "truth" he wants on Douyin, so he re-scrubbed his Weibo and tried to get closer to the "truth" . A large number of letters for help, was not admitted to the hospital... to see the hospital nurses crying video, nearly 30-year-old Huang Xingyang cried.
"All indications are that the situation in Wuhan is still very bad, and it may not get better in a short period of time. "

On January 19, Clefairy and her husband's more than 100 relatives and friends from Harbin, Guangzhou, Wuhan and other places rushed to Huanggang, attended Clefairy's wedding, and returned home. When all the relatives and friends finished their journey and turned on the TV at home to watch the news, the "preventable and controllable" and "limited human-to-human transmission" of new pneumonia broke out in Wuhan, resulting in "human-to-human transmission" and "infection of 15 medical staff. ".
"Now that I think about it, I'm still afraid. Fortunately, none of my relatives or friends were infected, " said Clefairy, who was worried about the recent wedding after learning that the outbreak might have spread earlier than expected and was even more severe. The local epidemic and related government initiatives have become a particular concern for Clefairy.

On the night of the wedding, Clefairy sent out a thank you to friends and family

Huanggang, 75 km from Wuhan, is the second-worst City in the province. The 700,000 people returning home from the city have put Huanggang, an economically underdeveloped region, at risk of becoming "the next Wuhan" .
On January 29, the slogan "never let Huanggang become a second Wuhan! " Gave hope to Huanggang people like Clefairy. But the next day, on television, the head of the commission made the slogan a question mark in Huanggang minds.
Before delving into the reasons for the commission's response, Clefairy was quick to note Huanggang's rapidly rising number of confirmed cases. "The numbers at this point feel real to me, because I know there are thirty new confirmed cases in Huangmei County every day. "
At 2400 hours on February 1,276 new cases were confirmed in Huanggang, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 1,002(data source: thepaper.cn) , making it the second city after Wuhan to break 1,000.
By the end of the first 14 days, Clefairy was back online. Still in the town of Oike, she was both a newlywed and an ordinary Huanggang citizen watching the outbreak in little pond. When the days were not counted in 14-day increments, Clefairy and his friends made a wish to become "super rich, " and "no overtime" would satisfy them. After the "first 14 days" began, "to live actively and healthily" became their greatest wish.
"The second 14 days is more important. If you don't get through it, there will be another 14 days. The uncertainty is frightening. "

On January 11, after nearly a week back in Hong Lake, the orange saw the full moon, a big, round moon. Two weeks from now, New Year's Eve, Crescent Moon. At three o'clock in the morning, orange lay in bed, tossing and turning for fear of the first-line medical staff.

Orange's January 11 circle of Friends: "You look at the moon. It's big and round. "

On January 23, the "first 14 days" against the "epidemic" began. Orange's high school classmates set up a wechat group with the name "Xi Ming Youth Bao Ping An. ". At this time, the word "peace" , for the Group of 11 Youth of the POST-00, more valuable than freedom. The epidemic has also become the focus of their daily attention.
The images of paramedics with their noses and cheeks frayed by masks, the news of an infection among front line workers, the growing number of confirmed and suspected cases... Close Your eyes and the images and figures start to come to mind. Instead of the usual bustle, the Hong Lake at night is quiet, but the orange is the one with the loudest voices of worry and anxiety.

"I'm too scared to sleep. "
"I can't sleep. I can't really sleep... "
"pathetic, weak, helpless. "
â€¦â€¦

February 6, the end of the first 14 days. Since the 29th, I only share my daily life in the daytime. I seldom send orange to my friends in the evening. After 10:00 pm, I retweeted "go honghu" -- a video made by two young people in Hong Lake -- to feel like a friend circle.

"Honghu refueling" by Liu Chengjie and Wang Yuhao

"there was no traffic or pedestrians on the way home, " says the video, which shows Hong Lake "in deep silence. ". In the morning, there were no people lining up to buy bean skin on Yusha road. In the evening, there were no couples dancing in Lotus Square

An orange shot of the outdoor KTV at Honghu River Beach Park

But in the view of the young people of Hong Lake, "the silence also represents the power of Hong Lake" . Medical staff on the front line, local volunteers to help, traffic police to stick to road checkpoints, Guangxi Nanning to help Hong Lake more than 200 tons of fruits and vegetables, including 31,000 boxes of Guangxi specialty spiral lion powder..

Image courtesy of Honghu refueling

On February 7, the first day of the second 14 days, Hong Lake's version of Little Tangshan began receiving patients. Two new cases have been confirmed in Hong Lake, the fewest new cases in 15 days.
Hong Lake was still quiet that night, and the orange was less restless.

"I'll show you my workbench! I'm Zoe from DONGTA, Guangzhou. " Trapped in the Tianmen smoke, in the first 14 days of January 23, ran into the Tianmen set down the "The F.B.I. , " originally thought and Guangzhou is in a hurry, the result of a sleepy, is more than 20 days.

I have a meeting with my colleagues in Guangzhou at this desk every day

Every year back to Tianmen New Year's smoking, the original plan to accompany the elderly to eat dinner on the train back to Guangzhou. As a result, on the afternoon of New Year's Eve, the city of Tianmen was also closed, and even the village could not get out after buying the tickets for the first day of the Lunar New Year and returning to Guangzhou.

Living in an old house built 50 years ago, there are no indoor toilets, only outdoor outhouses. There was no shower, just a big Tub, the house was drafty, and even some of the roofs leaked rain. "The biggest difficulty is the cold, the air is cold, the body is cold, the keyboard is cold, the network is not good. " From the beginning of the third day of the work task of pumping, it is difficult to sit down to work, work efficiency is only 1 / 5 of the usual.

"The leaders in the group push us to sign a contract, but I can't even take a bath when I get my period, and I don't know where to buy Sanitary Napkins! I haven't changed a set of clothes for more than ten days... " a few days before I arrived at Tianmen, a few coughs, a twitch, isolated in a more remote house. Facing a wasteland open computer, draw received the next day on-line start notice.

A smoking bed and a Brazier by my desk

Ordinary life is very simple to smoke, the material requirements are not high. Trapped in the village, she just want to take a hot bath, change into more than ten days of clothes, down-to-earth work.
"The first 14 days" in the smoke, more than once issued "I really want to go back to the city" feeling. If this is a metamorphosis, there's been plenty of smoking. Smoking cigarettes was one of her few pleasures.
"The second 14 days" began, from the town to draw a family to send food uncle, also trapped in the village, even without a change of clothes. The isolation in the village is getting worse, but the pumping is getting calmer.

Trapped for over 20 days, I walked to the entrance of the village for the first time.

"The sun came out the day before yesterday, I went to my aunt's house to have a bath, and after I came back, I had a coke. I was super happy! " There were still many difficulties at work, but at this time the twitch will choose to go out to the fields to walk, "pick firewood, followed my aunt to steal some vegetables in the fields. I can make a fire now! "
The "metamorphosis" of smoking is still going on in Tianmen, although I don't know how long it will continue, but she rarely complains to her friends about the inconvenience of village life. "The village chief came to sell eggs the other day. Fifty cents a piece. WE BOUGHT SIXTY! "
When the urge is low, the pleasure threshold becomes lower.

The second 14 days had begun, and Didi's second prenatal check up was taking longer and longer. But now she's afraid to leave the house.
On Jan. 7, Didi, who was three months pregnant, went to the hospital for her first checkup wearing a mask. "At the end of December, I learned from a friend that there were about 44 infected people in Wuhan, " she said. She wasn't sure if the news was true, but her trust in her friend and her protection of her baby, Didi, alerted new mothers. She reminded her husband to wear masks when he went out and stockpiled some.
A month ago the "gossip" was confirmed, the epidemic in the direction of more than expected development. With her baby, Didi couldn't believe it was actually happening to her. "I'm having a baby, so why did it happen to us? It's a scene from a movie, but in real life. "
"Do not visit, do not Dragon Lion Dance... ... " outside the window of the big speakers all rolling broadcast the epidemic-related warning slogans, the street empty, very quiet. Looking out the window, Didi couldn't see what was real.
Didi, who doesn't like to be cooped up in the house, likes to walk around and see, "I wouldn't mind going to another room, just don't let me stay in one place too long. " Didi, who can't go out, goes to the movies, put yourself in a different world.
Infectious Diseases, influenza... Didi watched every movie that looked like this. After experiencing the movie in Real Life, Didi chose to review the animation again and again. "I don't think I'm going to talk to my children about what I'm going through, " she said. "I want to talk about the good things. After all, there's more good things in the world. "

Didi's three new friends: Jimmy, the Black Chick, and blacky

Even though shopping wasn't easy, there were always dishes Didi liked. A trio of dogs named Jimmy, black girl, and black treasure are Didi's new main characters, and her husband has never been around this long... a window separates the real world from the Real, and Didi wants the time to pass and the time to stay.
"I'm a homebody, and I go back to Huangshi's house every half-month in Wuhan, and I skype with my mom every two or three days. " The second 14 days have started, and Didi wants to go home, i want to talk about my work, my life and my paintings with my mother as before.
"I want to go back to my normal life, " was Didi's most modest wish.

Didi used to share her drawings with her mom

At 10:00 on January 23, Xiantao and Wuhan Simultaneously "closed the city. ". On January 19, Liu returned to his hometown of Xiantao and witnessed how Xiantao was "isolated" step by step.
Xiantao "closed city" that day, the City Street traffic lights all lit up a red light, residential and residential roads between the road, there are vehicles. Later, the "home of Wuhan home members, please do not come" more and more seals appear in some people's door. Frequent communication with the "storm center" keeps Xiantao on high alert.
Xiantao, with an outflow of 403,500 people (2017 figure) , has migrant workers and students in every household similar to Liu. Wuhan, more than 100 kilometers away and less than 2 hours by car, has become the second home of many Xiantao people, with huge population movements taking place between the two cities.
Because of the outbreak, Xiantao and Wuhan Ground Connection was blocked, but the two places were not cut off.

Not by land. On the roof by air. At 5:37 p.m. on Feb. 1, a helicopter carrying more than 3,000 protective suits and more than 24,000 medical masks landed at Xinhua Road Stadium. Three days later, at 12:30 p.m. , the helicopter with 30,000 masks took off again from Xiantao airport.
The same "connection in the sky" happened to Liu and 31 families in Wuhan: Ask Online about Children's and parents' health, record parent-child Games, and share graphic stories on wechat groups. The lovely children in the screen, so that teacher Liu can not wait to return to Wuhan, to start work.

The first day of online teaching is also the first day that Miss Liu wants to work

â€”

The first 14 days are over. The second 14 days have begun.

Over the past 20 days, the number of confirmed cases in provinces other than Hubei has declined for the seventh consecutive day. However, the number of confirmed and additional suspected cases in Hubei Province is still increasing in fluctuation.
Hubei people face together, is a "protracted war epidemic. ". Wuhan is not the only battlefield, nor is the war epidemic confined to hospitals. Every ordinary Hubei who tries his best to maintain a normal life is a soldier who holds fast to the defense line.
It's not easy to live every 14 days. But in the past, we've won.

February 6, the end of the first 14 days. Since the 29th, I only share my daily life in the daytime. I seldom send orange to my friends in the evening. After 10:00 pm, I retweeted "go honghu" -- a video made by two young people in Hong Lake -- to feel like a friend circle.

"Honghu refueling" by Liu Chengjie and Wang Yuhao

"there was no traffic or pedestrians on the way home, " says the video, which shows Hong Lake "in deep silence. ". In the morning, there were no people lining up to buy bean skin on Yusha road. In the evening, there were no couples dancing in Lotus Square

"I'll show you my workbench! I'm Zoe from DONGTA, Guangzhou. " Trapped in the Tianmen smoke, in the first 14 days of January 23, ran into the Tianmen set down the "The F.B.I. , " originally thought and Guangzhou is in a hurry, the result of a sleepy, is more than 20 days.

I have a meeting with my colleagues in Guangzhou at this desk every day

Every year back to Tianmen New Year's smoking, the original plan to accompany the elderly to eat dinner on the train back to Guangzhou. As a result, on the afternoon of New Year's Eve, the city of Tianmen was also closed, and even the village could not get out after buying the tickets for the first day of the Lunar New Year and returning to Guangzhou.

Living in an old house built 50 years ago, there are no indoor toilets, only outdoor outhouses. There was no shower, just a big Tub, the house was drafty, and even some of the roofs leaked rain. "The biggest difficulty is the cold, the air is cold, the body is cold, the keyboard is cold, the network is not good. " From the beginning of the third day of the work task of pumping, it is difficult to sit down to work, work efficiency is only 1 / 5 of the usual.

"The leaders in the group push us to sign a contract, but I can't even take a bath when I get my period, and I don't know where to buy Sanitary Napkins! I haven't changed a set of clothes for more than ten days... " a few days before I arrived at Tianmen, a few coughs, a twitch, isolated in a more remote house. Facing a wasteland open computer, draw received the next day on-line start notice.

The second 14 days had begun, and Didi's second prenatal check up was taking longer and longer. But now she's afraid to leave the house.
On Jan. 7, Didi, who was three months pregnant, went to the hospital for her first checkup wearing a mask. "At the end of December, I learned from a friend that there were about 44 infected people in Wuhan, " she said. She wasn't sure if the news was true, but her trust in her friend and her protection of her baby, Didi, alerted new mothers. She reminded her husband to wear masks when he went out and stockpiled some.
A month ago the "gossip" was confirmed, the epidemic in the direction of more than expected development. With her baby, Didi couldn't believe it was actually happening to her. "I'm having a baby, so why did it happen to us? It's a scene from a movie, but in real life. "
"Do not visit, do not Dragon Lion Dance... ... " outside the window of the big speakers all rolling broadcast the epidemic-related warning slogans, the street empty, very quiet. Looking out the window, Didi couldn't see what was real.
Didi, who doesn't like to be cooped up in the house, likes to walk around and see, "I wouldn't mind going to another room, just don't let me stay in one place too long. " Didi, who can't go out, goes to the movies, put yourself in a different world.
Infectious Diseases, influenza... Didi watched every movie that looked like this. After experiencing the movie in Real Life, Didi chose to review the animation again and again. "I don't think I'm going to talk to my children about what I'm going through, " she said. "I want to talk about the good things. After all, there's more good things in the world. "

At 10:00 on January 23, Xiantao and Wuhan Simultaneously "closed the city. ". On January 19, Liu returned to his hometown of Xiantao and witnessed how Xiantao was "isolated" step by step.
Xiantao "closed city" that day, the City Street traffic lights all lit up a red light, residential and residential roads between the road, there are vehicles. Later, the "home of Wuhan home members, please do not come" more and more seals appear in some people's door. Frequent communication with the "storm center" keeps Xiantao on high alert.
Xiantao, with an outflow of 403,500 people (2017 figure) , has migrant workers and students in every household similar to Liu. Wuhan, more than 100 kilometers away and less than 2 hours by car, has become the second home of many Xiantao people, with huge population movements taking place between the two cities.
Because of the outbreak, Xiantao and Wuhan Ground Connection was blocked, but the two places were not cut off.

The first 14 days are over. The second 14 days have begun.

Over the past 20 days, the number of confirmed cases in provinces other than Hubei has declined for the seventh consecutive day. However, the number of confirmed and additional suspected cases in Hubei Province is still increasing in fluctuation.
Hubei people face together, is a "protracted war epidemic. ". Wuhan is not the only battlefield, nor is the war epidemic confined to hospitals. Every ordinary Hubei who tries his best to maintain a normal life is a soldier who holds fast to the defense line.
It's not easy to live every 14 days. But in the past, we've won.
